<p>A panel part of a solid model consists of an obverse surface, a reverse surface and the in-between zone having a thickness.<br>The three types of data are almost always integrated in the form of panel.<br>When you wish to use only the obverse side data, you need to remove the in-between and reverse side and transfer them to other layers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h5><strong>Fetures</strong></h5><p><strong>For the situations above</strong></p><p>An easy way to release the obverse surface is to execute the &quot;Separate&quot; command and specify &lsquo;Tangent&rsquo; in the palette window of the command.</p><ul><li>If the elements of a solid model have been disintegrated, execute the &quot;CompSrf_Connect&quot; subcommand of the tool bar of &#39;Surface&#39; in order to integrate them.</li><li>Execute the &quot;CompSrf_Separate&quot; subcommand of the tool bar of &#39;Surface&#39;.</li><li>Specify a subject part of the solid model and right-click in order to display a context menu. Choose [Tangent] in the context menu.</li></ul><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/7.CASE%20STUDY/1.Top%20and%20below/Top%20and%20below1.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><ul><li>Enter &#39;89&deg;&#39; in the column of &#39;Angle tolerance (degree)&#39;.</li></ul><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/7.CASE%20STUDY/1.Top%20and%20below/Top%20and%20below2.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><ul><li>And, the presence of obverse surface is expressly indicated by the red dotted lines in the above figure.<br>The obverse side is positioned on the top side of the in-between part.</li><li>Center-click on the obverse surface and release it.</li><li>Execute the &quot;Layer&quot; command in order to transfer to any other layers the elements that have been left behind.</li></ul><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/7.CASE%20STUDY/1.Top%20and%20below/Top%20and%20below3.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"> <img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/7.CASE%20STUDY/1.Top%20and%20below/Top%20and%20below4.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p>